Crack Repair Procedure:   1. Route out and clean all the cracks.  Prep the concrete at least 2 inches on each side of the crack.  We will use a diamond grinder.  2. Prime the joint as well as 2 inches on either side of the joint using Sikaflex Primer 429.  Sika 2cNS requires a primer of sealant will be subjected to water immersion after cure.  3. Place the right size backer rod or fill with the 2cNS.  We will use the 2cNS.  4.  Apply the Sika 2cNS over all primed areas.  3. Embed a 4" fiberglass mesh into the 2cNS using a Rib Roller.  Some prefer using a trowel or drywall knife but a rib roller works best in my opinion.  4. Apply more 2cNS to fully encapsulate everything.
